########################
Modules needed
########################
Bioperl
- see bioperl.org. Need Bio::Seq, Bio::SeqIO, Bio::Root::Root.

Bio::DB::EUtilities
- https://github.com/bioperl/Bio-EUtilities.

Bio::LITE::Taxonomy
 - version 0.07 http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/M/MO/MOTIF/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-0.07.tar.gz
Bio::LITE::Taxonomy::NCBI
 - version 0.08 or 0.1 http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/M/MO/MOTIF/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI-0.08.tar.gz
Bio::LITE::Taxonomy::NCBI::Gi2taxid
 - version 0.1 http://search.cpan.org/CPAN/authors/id/M/MO/MOTIF/Bio-LITE-Taxonomy-NCBI-Gi2taxid-0.10.tar.gz
   (MacOSX). However there were problems with 0.1 on Linux so use version 0.06

XML::Simple - used by Taxonomy.pm

plus other dependencies like URI, HTTP::Request, ... that are needed by the
above modules


#######################
Environmental variables
#######################
Set the following ENVIRONMENT variables in your .profile:

BLASTDB - directory of blast databases
NGT - /path/to/gi_taxid_nucl.bin
PGT - /path/to/gi_taxid_prot.bin
NAMESDMP - /path/to/names.dmp
NODESDMP - /path/to/nodes.dmp

PATH
Add this folder and bin/ to your PATH.

PERL5LIB
Add this folder and 'Annotator' to PERL5LIB. Additionally, add the
directories for the required modules (see above) to PERL5LIB.


################
Taxonomy database
################

# get new Taxonomy files
wget --quiet ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/taxonomy/gi_taxid_nucl.dmp.gz &
wget --quiet ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/taxonomy/gi_taxid_prot.dmp.gz &
wget --quiet ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/taxonomy/taxdump.tar.gz &
wget --quiet ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pub/taxonomy/taxcat.tar.gz &

# unzip each GZ file
for file in *gz; do echo $file; gunzip $file; done

# untar the tar archives
tar xvf taxcat.tar
tar xvf taxdump.tar

# remove GZ archives
rm -f *gz

# convert DMP file to BIN file for Bio::LITE::Taxonomy::NCBI::Gi2taxid module
# see https://github.com/pcantalupo/mytaxonomy
makebin.pl &
